The participants of auctions are likely to spend more money and overstate the product. 
The neurólogos and economists from the University of New York discovered the neurological basis - economic of this conduct known and seemingly irrational. 
According to the study published in the journal Science, the people do not want to lose in authority as eBay auctions, so prefers to pay even overpriced. 
Scientists tried to establish the neurological system of this "game" by means of experimental auction. 
One of the groups of volunteers working lottery, the other was involved in an auction and meanwhile was examined by the system of functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) areas of the brain are active participants in the experiment. 
In both games could earn money participants, but during the auction, which is fundamental to bet more than the other, to lose the game intensified the functioning of the complex called layer located below the cerebral cortex. 
This area of the brain, as well as many other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of "car prize" of the nervous system. 
So according to the scientists, the rise of the stakes can be explained as a prevention not to provoke a reaction by the body of intense. 
To establish his theory, economists of scientific group also made a study of financial follow-up. 
In this experiment three groups who bet against a person in different circumstances. 
The control group was simply told the real value of the product in question, and their members who bet. 
Another group also promised that if you earn, would receive $15 more of prize. 
In exchange, the third group received exactly 15 dollars before the auction, but in the event of losing the auction the members of the group perdían even money. 
