However, tested the hypothesis of the neurólogos, the members of the group that appeared "against the failure" were willing to bet even more than the members of the group and the control group "winner". 
"These results cannot be deducted from any existing economic theory. 
Because those until now explicaban the phenomena of auctions solely with the joy of winning and with the prevention of risks. 
Only the methods neurologically impaired helped resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so that now we come to a third explanation "- established Andrew Schotter, professor of economics faculty of the University of New York. 
